  <SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="pvm_tidtohost"> returns the host of the specified PVM process.  </SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>[dtid] = pvm_tidtohost(tid)  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  </CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <PARAM>
 <PARAM_INDENT>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>tid  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
    : integer, task identifier of the PVM process in question.
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>dtid  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
    : integer, the tid of the host&apos;s pvmd3 or a negative value if an error.
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
 </PARAM_INDENT>
  </PARAM>
  <DESCRIPTION>
  <P>
  </P>
  <P>
    <VERB>pvm_tidtohost</VERB> returns the host id on which the process identified by
  </P>
  <P>
  </P>
  <P>
  </P>
